{
  "texts": [
    "The claim presupposed by P3 is not that AGI might lack the capacity for moral reasoning.",
    "For all we know, AGI might necessarily be better than humans in moral reasoning, as manifested in the capacity to, e.g., write ethics papers.",
    "The claim is not that AGI would lack any ability, but that it might lack ethical goals.",
    "While being able to reason ethically, AGI would not have any motivation to act ethically if that is not its goal.",
    "While open to debate, the claim that goals and abilities to achieve goals are largely independent in AI is supported by current ML approaches."
  ]
}